\subsection{Standardised Protocol}
The protocol that will be followed consists on 3 steps. Firstly, the initial state must be prepared. Then standard RB will be applied, followed by the procedures for survival probability estimation. Finally, gate error will be calculated.

\begin{enumerate}[start=0]
    \item Fixing the initial state $|\psi\rangle$ \\
    The initial state will be set as $|\psi\rangle=|0\rangle$, as standard.\\
    \item Standard RB implementation
    The Clifford group will be defined according to.
    \item Interleaving a specific gate
    \item Gate Error estimation
\end{enumerate}
\begin{align}
F^{(0)}_{\text{seq}}(m, \psi) &= A_0 p^m + B_0, \\
F^{(1)}_{\text{seq}}(m, \psi) &= A_1 p^m + C_1 (m-1) p^{m-2} + B_1, \nonumber
\end{align}


